Knowing how the Brell populace seems to be contesting raid schedules more and more these days, I'm not too eager to throw in something new to chew over (or get chewed over), but I guess I should still try to work with the system.  So here goes.<br>
<br>
Over the life of my main character I've been cultivating a roleplay story for him as much as I've gameplayed him to level and loot.  And now my character is on the cusp of hitting 46th level.  For roleplaying purposes I feel it is important to send my character headlong into Fear soonafter that level rings out.  Likely alone.<br>
<br>
This may seem crazy, and either way the reasons for doing this are irrelevant to get into here, (aside: if you're really curious, then catch me in game and roleplay with me for awhile to get some clues).  Basically, it's going to happen sometime in the next few weeks or so, and I want to make sure there's enough of a chance to discuss ideas on how best to make it work.  I'm assuming that a lot of people probably don't want random plane newbies running around training Cazic's minions during their scheduled raid time.<br>
<br>
Certainly, I want to keep from interfering with the raid schedule.  But I generally wouldn't accept that there is no room on the schedule for roleplay.  And I really don't need much room to squeeze this in.<br>
<br>
Any ideas? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uphazy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phazy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/24/01 8:55:38 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: No room for roleplay?</span><hr size=1> Actually its  simple.<br>
<br>
You run in. You take 2 steps. The mobs that see through invis say &quot;Lunch&quot; you die after taking 2 more steps. You go back for body. You die. Rinse repeat. <br>
<br>
&lt;ooc in case you didnt know there are GOBS of mobs arounf the port in area..and the portal is one way. The only ways out are being ported, or a run through the temple...and no way you will make it if mobs are in it.&gt;<br>
<br>
If you went up AFTER a raid was finished probably wouldn't upset anyone, and you wouldnt die in 2 seconds. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uthoricthemad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thoric the Mad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Brell's man of Nomex</span><br>  Posts: 204<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/26/01 2:42:10 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: No room for roleplay?</span><hr size=1> Actually you should come pull for our next raid... a crazy newbie training Cazic's minions bears a great resemblance to our insane chanters pulling more mobs just to see how many they can keep mezzed. You'll save tanix, kendon, et. al. a lot of footwork.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nojo>Nojo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/26/01 7:28:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: No room for roleplay?</span><hr size=1> <br>
Heh.  I certainly agree that most likely I'll be mulched within two steps.  Although there's a small chance that I can get through the entrance semi-ok.  I wouldn't be able to repeat though, since likely the xp loss will punt me back to 45.  But largely that's not the point.<br>
<br>
Really, I would prefer to not plan this at all, and start the ball rolling as soon as I'm conveniently ready.  And whatever state fear is in at that time is a coincidence to deal with (hopefully with roleplay).  But I want to avoid undermining the work people have put into organizing and administrating the raid guidelines.  If coincidentally a raid is in effect when I would hit fear, it probably would be dangerous of me to be running around, flailing my arms, huge train on my heels.  Whether or not raid veterans have seen that sight a thousand times before.<br>
<br>
So basically, are there any suggestions as to how to fit in this kind of goal in the raid guidelines?  Do people care if unknown chars zone in randomly during their scheduled turns on the planes?  Does anyone insist that fear is off limits unless you're in on a raid?  Let's discuss. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uselilya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>selilya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Winnower of the Harvest</span><br>  Posts: 343<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/26/01 7:57:15 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/selilya/sel_head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: No room for roleplay?</span><hr size=1> The raid hosts are listed for the next two weeks.  You'd have to coordinate something like this with them.  Not coordinating could likely ruin the Fear experience for 30 to 42 folks who have made diligent preparation to be there.<br>
<br>
As an avid RP'er, and an Officer in an evil RP guild, we would never intentionally ruin the experience of those not involved in our particular storyline.  Folks respect our right to roleplay...heck...our attack on Kelethin was pretty good evidence of that.<br>
<br>
There are, perhaps, better times than others to attempt Fear.  After a raid is done, the zone will be clear for some time.  Re-pops are usually 12 or so hours later.  One thing to consider...if you zone in alone and die, getting your corpse back might be a challenge...you'd have to again coordinate with a hosting guild.<br>
<br>
Good luck to you.  If you wish to check out our version of roleplay, look us up ingame...or visit our website at:<br>
<br>
