Selilya Ka`Trael<br>
Winnower of the Violent Harvest<br>
Devoted Daughter of Innoruuk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueoralsolis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EoralSolis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 168<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/27/01 1:15:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: No room for roleplay?</span><hr size=1> Selilya's point is well taken, and there are many who value RP.  I would like to reiterate one thing that she has said though.  THe raids for the next two weeks are on the schedule, including the guild and raid leader.  Why are you not contacting them in game and working something out rather than come here?  No tthat you are not welcome, of course you are, but if you do not want to inconvenience anyone, why not talk to the folks hosting the raids?  I am sure a reasonable solution can be found.<br>
<br>
Eoral Solis<br>
Servant of Evoluxa <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nojo>Nojo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/27/01 8:48:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: No room for roleplay?</span><hr size=1> <br>
Yes.  Selilya's words are wise and persuasive.  I might be mistaken in assuming that today's Brell guilds on plane raids would aggressively and perhaps unfairly discourage actions for which they have no responsibility, (ie, 'ruin the experience' of others).  Personally, I've experienced secondhand some of the worst guild politics and gm behaviour this server's ever seen.  But, that was some time ago.<br>
<br>
Reconsidering this, I might be more willing to coordinate with the scheduled raidmasters outside of roleplay.  However, I am still worried about this approach for several reasons that are essentially side issues at the moment.  But the biggest reason I'm worried is that currently my position has no weight in the rules.  I'm essentially at the mercy of the raidmasters, or else I intentionally disrespect their position and do what I want anyway without a care, (except I would care, turning my roleplay excursion into a guilt trip).<br>
<br>
If there is room in the plane raid scheduling guidelines that can cover non-raid uses of fear, I would then know how to make it work before having to cooperate with or negotiate with anyone else for plane privilege.<br>
<br>
For example, Selilya suggested the possibility of timing such non-raid uses to occur only after the scheduled raid was complete.  As I understand fear raids, this would mean timing for early-to-mid morning in general.  If that's workable as a rule for the raiding parties I can accept that, though personally I know it's far too inconvenient for me to take advantage of in my case.  Still if that's something I can get then I'd be pleased with having something to try to work with.<br>
<br>
Still, there can be a lot to keep in mind for making such rules.  What if I not only survive my initial entry into Fear, but manage to pull off a major upset and kill some epic spawn (in the flow of roleplay)?  That spawn may then not be available for the next raid.  I'm sure some people may not be too happy with that, and I doubt they'd be eager to simply roleplay out their displeasure.<br>
<br>
I find it fairly unfortunate that EQ is stacked against roleplay in the first place.  I mean, mobs that can flee through walls before you can say 'I have you cornered now, vile orc'?  Bard npcs that can't sing a lick?  No levitation in the Plane of Air (is Noble Dojorn afraid of heights or what)?  I certainly concede that in order to do anything meaningfully epic in EQ one has to largely abandon roleplay and come down to the basic raid gameplay.  I've managed to sneak in a lot of my style of roleplay but at the higher levels its getting hard.  I'm just hoping that there is some room I can work with to both get my enjoyment out of the game without interfering with that of others.<br>
<br>
With that said, I can return to practical tactics for a moment.  I certainly have on my mind how tough corpse retrieval would be in my plans.  I'm well aware how likely it is that should I die, my corpse would decay and I'd lose whatever equipment was on it.  In terms of roleplay I would accept that, (as would any travelling mercenary who might happen to join up with me).  I may yet decide that it makes roleplay sense to equip my normal gear (decent Ro/Kunark stuff) for the raid, even if it all decays.  Be assured that I'm trying to be as diligent in my roleplay preparations as the scheduled raid leaders are being in their raid plans.  <br>
<br>
After all, we all have the same goal to get the most out of the plane experience as possible.  I just have a different approach today, and to be honest I'm looking forward to see what happens with it.<br>
<br>
...<br>
