My suggestion:  Go buy banded armor, and a FS 2h sword, then rush in! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uorri.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Orri</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fire Brand</span><br>  Posts: 455<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/28/01 5:09:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: No room for roleplay?</span><hr size=1> I guess my question is, why do you want to roleplay a suicide?<br>
<br>
I like roleplaying alot; how a character talks, who they have faction with, remembering people like you are creating a 'history'.<br>
<br>
But this, this is beyond my imagination. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nojo>Nojo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/30/01 8:19:12 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: No room for roleplay?</span><hr size=1> Heh, I guess I can talk a bit more about where my character's coming from.<br>
<br>
Why would I want to roleplay a suicide?  That's not really an easy question to answer, even if I have a good reason.  I have reasons, but I wouldn't know how good they are.<br>
<br>
First, though, I don't really consider it suicide when the character will just respawn back at the bind point.  That's just an inescapable roleplay-non-sequitur.  All I'm potentially risking is what equipment I bring with me, and even if I do lose quest armor, it gives me a hook for future campaigning with my character.<br>
<br>
Yes, it does seem obvious that the character will not survive the encounter.  But, in terms of roleplay, no puny mortal born of common Norrathian lineage who enters &quot;The Plane of Fear&quot; (cue ominous thunder) should expect to survive this experience, and furthermore they should only expect to go insane from the terror upon zone-in.  Wouldn't you agree that an Erudite standing next to Cazic-Thule is just a bit overmatched?  From this perspective, every character on every fear raid every day is thus suicidal.  I don't think this is too unimaginable.<br>
<br>
From my character's perspective, he is somewhat motivated to confront his own worst fears, (there is a significant history behind this, but it's not important here for now).  Currently, it's an easy assumption for him to make that to do so, he must confront the lord of fear, Cazic-Thule himself.  This was never an option to him before (due to the level-46 entry limitation), but it has become more glaringly obvious over the last few weeks (real time, months in Norrath time) as the character surges through the twilight of 45.  <br>
<br>
From my perspective, I remember reading a report of a player a long time ago.  The report detailed an amazing roleplay battle between the gm-controlled daughter of an evil god, (I forget which) and a player-controlled virtuous character.  I don't recall much of the details of the battle, but it was hard fought, going over several zones and multiple days.  The evil character would suggest duelling rules and then break them, and in the end the player prevailed by nobly removing all armor and weapons and intentionally making himself vulnerable in the best tradition of his own religion.  If she were to strike him down, his god would win from his noble sacrifice.  If she were not to strike him down, her father would punish her for failing to perform in the tradition of his religion.  Or something like that.  It was an amazing read and I took from that that there's a lot more potential in EQ play than just to loot uber weapons off the corpse of Cazic-Thule.  But, that was a long time ago.<br>
<br>
I've also recently reread the list of god descriptions and suggested roles to play when following the various gods.  It's interesting reading and it has reminded me of various roleplay obligations my characters have.  (How can followers of Innoruuk and Karana manage to group together in Kedge Keep?  It boggles the character's mind.)<br>
<br>
Objectively, it's hard to believe that I'd pull off anything like that, but it's probably worth a try just to see what might happen.  If other people are interested in seeing what might happen, I'm not opposed to them coming, but I have no guild, and as such I won't be doing much of that kind of organizing.  This is about roleplay more than gameplay, (I hope). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhethral.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hethral</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/r Where's the corpse.</span><br>  Posts: 1269<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/30/01 4:45:05 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://the.truthbringers.com/Images/Members/HeadShots/HethralHead2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: No room for roleplay?</span><hr size=1> Nojo, talk to a raid leader who's raid is starting a lil later than you get home. Log on, zone in, run like mad and see how many things you can pull / get killed by at once. Everything paths back, the raid starts, and either once they get to you or once the raids over you get your body back. You get to play in a fully popped fear and noone gets put out.<br>
<br>
I'm sure most leaders wouldn't mind you going in _before_ they start, just so long as things have time to wander back you won't be disturbing them any. I know most groups I've raided with would let you if you ask ahead of time. <p><CENTER>Hethral Kegslayer - 53rd level Cleric for Hire</CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utagarth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tagarth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/30/01 5:14:54 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: No room for roleplay?</span><hr size=1> What you are talking about are the events that led to the 'creation' of a rift into the plane of hate. yeh, it is one of the coolest things they have done with eq.<br>
<br>
Maybe the stuff going on in the karanas will be like that, dunno.<br>
<br>
